result.adr_address: 28 Elgin St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Posto Pubblico

reviews.text: Nice friendly casual place. Nice choice of cocktails and wines. Food menu looked good but wasn't eating so can't comment on quality but the dishes being served looked good. Friendly staff and attentive without being overbearing.

Plant based meal review.
Food was ok, but felt it was pricey for what was delivered. The deep fried enoki mushrooms were so-so. Lacking good seasoning and could have been more adventurous than tasting of batter. Posto Pubblico is renowned for its red sauce and the eggplant pasta dish I ordered was tasty, but where was the eggplant? Was it all blended up? Pasta was overcooked and very soft. Too soft. Ended up pretty hungry afterwards as portion sizes weren't exactly going to fill me up. Decent service, but the food is what matters most to me.
It’s poor. Seems to have changed ownership and quality has gone down significantly. New owners need to speak to former and learn

Friendly waiter let us go in and sit down though we arrived a bit before opening hours. Food was okay and environment was nice at noon (we visited on a Saturday). Not too busy and hence not yet noisy at that hour

Nice atmosphere, ideal for families and group gathering. Best tomato burrata in town! We love it!
A bit pricey.
